The paper discusses the development of an algorithm for information filtering in online scientific communities, which involves analyzing a bipartite network of users and papers. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and digital libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multilayer networks and the evaluation of the algorithm on real data from the Econophysics Forum, which could indicate a focus on cyber-physical systems (cs.CYBER) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
